The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems, specifically perfect matching and maximum flow, in graphs that are defined by forbidding a certain type of minor, namely one-crossing minors. This makes it likely that the paper would be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves results related to planar graphs and graphs of bounded genus, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, such as the use of matching-mimicking networks, which could make it relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
